[The close and constrained environment of prison can be quite conducive to rapid spread of infectious diseases such as chickenpox to various sections of the facility as well as to the community. Isolation of confirmed cases during the infectious period can help contain the spread, and post-exposure vaccination should be considered in such settings. - Mod.UBA

